2. Define the overall goals and objectives of the software.
3. Determine the key functionalities and features required.
4. Identify the entities and their relationships in the software.
5. Design the user interface and user experience.

7. Define the algorithms and logic required to implement the functionalities.
8. Determine the external systems or services that the software will interact with.
9. Define the security measures and access control requirements.
10. Consider scalability and performance requirements.
11. Plan for testing and quality assurance.
